{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 4",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-600500557395788437 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/j0rgbv-09/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=600495993187730277&sectionId=600500557395788437)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4kNbQ0iOE_text","label":"gg4kNbQ0iOE_text","default":"In Italy, we've approached men's aging differently for generations."},{"type":"html","id":"gg6J8ky7lD8_text","label":"gg6J8ky7lD8_text","default":"<p>While American companies were busy slapping \"FOR MEN\" labels on women's moisturizers and calling it innovation, Italian pharmaceutical labs were asking a different question:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggj7C6LOfOQ_text","label":"ggj7C6LOfOQ_text","default":"<p><i>\"What does aging male skin actually need at the cellular level—and how do we deliver it without the side effects?\"</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3ZElSJ2x7_text","label":"gg3ZElSJ2x7_text","default":"<p>This isn't marketing. It's pharmaceutical science. And we've had decades to refine it.</p><p><br>Walk into any pharmacy in Rome, Milan, or Florence. Ask the pharmacist what he recommends for a man over 50 concerned about his neck.</p><p><br>You won't hear about moisturizers. You won't hear about beef tallow. You won't hear about harsh prescription Retinol.</p><p><br>You'll hear about something else entirely.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg0EcHm2YAu_text","label":"gg0EcHm2YAu_text","default":"The breakthrough: <span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Retinyl Palmitate</span>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggXhf_YZaYi_text","label":"ggXhf_YZaYi_text","default":"<p>In the 1980s, Italian dermatological researchers were studying Vitamin A derivatives. They knew that Retinoic Acid—the active form of Vitamin A—was the gold standard for collagen rebuilding. The science was clear.</p><p><br>But they also knew the problem: <strong>Retinoic Acid is too aggressive for most skin.</strong></p><p><br>It works by forcing immediate, rapid cell turnover. For young skin, this is tolerable. For mature skin—especially the thin, sensitive skin of the neck—it's often too much. Redness. Peeling. Inflammation. Damaged moisture barriers.</p><p><br>So they asked: <i>\"What if we could deliver the same collagen-building benefit, but through a gentler pathway?\"</i></p><p><br>The answer was <strong>Retinyl Palmitate.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggvP-hfgjQg_text","label":"ggvP-hfgjQg_text","default":"How Retinyl Palmitate works (for the skeptics who want to understand)"},{"type":"html","id":"ggF2D0jNb6w_text","label":"ggF2D0jNb6w_text","default":"<p>Retinyl Palmitate is what we call a \"pro-drug\" or precursor. It's not the active form of Vitamin A—it's one step removed.</p><p><br>Here's what happens when you apply it to your skin:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggbTuTqebLq_text","label":"ggbTuTqebLq_text","default":"<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 1:</span> Absorption</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggz_DcY9K-l_text","label":"ggz_DcY9K-l_text","default":"<p>Unlike harsh Retinol that attacks the surface immediately, Retinyl Palmitate absorbs slowly and deeply into the dermis—the structural layer of your skin where collagen actually lives.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsxYYUhP0l_text","label":"ggsxYYUhP0l_text","default":"<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 2:</span> Conversion</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggB1e6dCzij_text","label":"ggB1e6dCzij_text","default":"<p>Once inside, your skin's own enzymes convert Retinyl Palmitate into Retinol, then into Retinaldehyde, and finally into Retinoic Acid—the active compound that signals collagen production.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggglynBZ6wJ_text","label":"ggglynBZ6wJ_text","default":"<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 3:</span> Signaling</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggtQn0W-A3k_text","label":"ggtQn0W-A3k_text","default":"<p>The Retinoic Acid binds to receptors on your fibroblast cells. These are the \"construction workers\" of your skin. The signal tells them: <i>\"Start building new collagen.\"</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRO6euQIIk_text","label":"ggRO6euQIIk_text","default":"<p><span style=\"color:#0055B5;\">Step 4:</span> Rebuilding</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggdmJEfQCGx_text","label":"ggdmJEfQCGx_text","default":"<p>Your fibroblasts begin producing new Type I collagen—the same structural protein that's been degrading since you turned 50. Over 6-8 weeks, this new collagen accumulates, creating visible firming and tightening.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9UZj1vo5U_text","label":"gg9UZj1vo5U_text","default":"<p>The key difference? <strong>The conversion happens gradually, inside your skin.</strong></p><p><br>You get the same collagen-rebuilding benefit as harsh Retinol. But because the active compound is being released slowly, over time, there's no \"purge.\" No redness. No peeling. No embarrassing flaking at the office.</p><p><br>I call it <i>\"il retinolo del gentiluomo\"</i>—the gentleman's Retinol.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg2-jiY6j6b_text","label":"gg2-jiY6j6b_text","default":"But Retinyl Palmitate alone isn't enough."},{"type":"html","id":"gglxA_VI2Ls_text","label":"gglxA_VI2Ls_text","default":"<p>This is where most American products fail. They include one active ingredient at a low concentration and call it a day.</p><p><br>Italian pharmaceutical formulation is different. We think in systems.</p><p><br>If you're going to rebuild collagen, you need three things working together:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggmHrwtgs2f_text","label":"ggmHrwtgs2f_text","default":"<p>1. THE BUILDER:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggVHw1Bpvmf_text","label":"ggVHw1Bpvmf_text","default":"<p>Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A)</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5Sm_WoNZ7_text","label":"gg5Sm_WoNZ7_text","default":"<p>This is the primary signal. It tells your cells to produce new collagen. Without this, nothing else matters—you're just moisturizing a collapsing structure.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggCQZPk0vw5_text","label":"ggCQZPk0vw5_text","default":"<p>Function: Restarts collagen production at the cellular level</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggvslDUYn6k_text","label":"ggvslDUYn6k_text","default":"<p>2. THE REINFORCER:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRUTFSviA9_text","label":"ggRUTFSviA9_text","default":"<p>Stabilized Vitamin C</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggsOMXh8XZ2_text","label":"ggsOMXh8XZ2_text","default":"<p>Here's something most men don't know: newly produced collagen is fragile. It needs to be \"cross-linked\" and stabilized to become strong, durable structural protein.</p><p><br>Vitamin C is the essential cofactor for this process. It's like the difference between wet concrete and cured concrete. Without adequate Vitamin C, your new collagen won't set properly.</p><p><br>But here's the problem: Vitamin C is notoriously unstable. It oxidizes quickly when exposed to air and light. Most Vitamin C products have degraded significantly before they even reach your skin.</p><p><br>Italian labs solved this decades ago using stabilized forms—like Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate—that remain potent until the moment of application. The best formulations use Vitamin C derived from Sicilian blood oranges, which has a unique antioxidant profile.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggX9kCC9axZ_text","label":"ggX9kCC9axZ_text","default":"<p>Function: Strengthens and stabilizes new collagen fibers</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggEiSospYEG_text","label":"ggEiSospYEG_text","default":"<p>3. THE PROTECTOR:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggi_urbOWNu_text","label":"ggi_urbOWNu_text","default":"<p>Hyaluronic Acid</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwni7HxvFi_text","label":"ggwni7HxvFi_text","default":"<p>This is where most people misunderstand Hyaluronic Acid.</p><p><br>Yes, it hydrates. Yes, it \"plumps\" fine lines temporarily. But that's not why we include it.</p><p><br>The real function of Hyaluronic Acid in an anti-aging formulation is <strong>enzyme inhibition.</strong></p><p><br>Remember those MMPs I mentioned—the enzymes that break down collagen? Hyaluronic Acid has been shown to inhibit MMP activity. It's actively defending the collagen you're building from being broken down.</p><p><br>Think of it as posting a security guard at the construction site. You're building new structure with Retinyl Palmitate, strengthening it with Vitamin C, and protecting it from demolition with Hyaluronic Acid.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggv66qJ0Hsx_text","label":"ggv66qJ0Hsx_text","default":"<p>Function: Blocks collagen-destroying enzymes while providing deep hydration</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gggEkpXZx3M_text","label":"gggEkpXZx3M_text","default":"\"Costruzione e protezione\"—Building and protecting"},{"type":"html","id":"ggJZWJHbFDq_text","label":"ggJZWJHbFDq_text","default":"<p>This is the philosophy behind Italian anti-aging formulation. It's not enough to stimulate. You must also protect.</p><p><br>American products typically focus on one or the other. They'll give you a Retinol product (stimulation) and tell you to use a separate moisturizer (protection). Two products. Two price tags. Two opportunities for something to go wrong.</p><p><br>Italian pharmaceutical tradition combines them into a single, synergistic formula. One application. One ritual. Complete intervention.</p><p><br>And we apply it at night—when your skin's natural repair processes are most active. The circadian rhythm of cellular regeneration peaks between 11pm and 2am. That's when your skin is primed to receive these signals.</p><p><br><strong>This isn't complicated. It's just correct.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDphhZB9yI_text","label":"ggDphhZB9yI_text","default":"Why this matters specifically for the neck:"},{"type":"html","id":"ggW24EKL39R_text","label":"ggW24EKL39R_text","default":"<p>The skin on your neck has unique characteristics that make it particularly suited to this three-part approach:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_0","label":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_0","default":"<p><strong>Thinner epidermis </strong>— Gentler formulations absorb more efficiently without irritation</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_1","label":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_1","default":"<p><strong>Fewer sebaceous glands</strong> — Won't get clogged by heavy occlusives like beef tallow</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_2","label":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_2","default":"<p><strong>High MMP activity</strong> — Benefits significantly from the protective Hyaluronic Acid component</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_3","label":"ggPN8P0Hx02_childItem_3","default":"<p><strong>Visible structural framework </strong>— Responds dramatically to collagen rebuilding because there&#039;s less fat obscuring the underlying structure</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg2EGqLyoP2_text","label":"gg2EGqLyoP2_text","default":"<p>When men tell me their neck \"responded faster\" than their face, this is why. The neck shows structural changes more readily because there's less between the surface and the scaffolding underneath.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggtt2biO-LY_text","label":"ggtt2biO-LY_text","default":"What happened next surprised even me."},{"type":"html","id":"ggVxSsSCWX3_text","label":"ggVxSsSCWX3_text","default":"<p>Within 18 months, Omnis had become the #1 pharmacist recommendation for men over 40 in Italy. Not through television advertising or celebrity endorsements—through word of mouth among pharmacists and their patients.</p><p><br>Today, the numbers are difficult to ignore:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_0","label":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_0","default":"<p><strong>72,000+ Italian men</strong> have used this formulation</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_1","label":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_1","default":"<p><strong>7,405+ verified reviews </strong>with an average rating of 4.8 out of 5 stars</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_2","label":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_2","default":"<p><strong>#1 pharmacist recommendation </strong>for men's anti-aging in Italian pharmacies</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_3","label":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_3","default":"<p><strong>93% of users </strong>report visible improvement in skin firmness by week 8</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_4","label":"ggRyyqGslZz_childItem_4","default":"<p><strong>87%</strong> specifically note improvement in the neck and jawline area</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggZ9E6xBzUL_text","label":"ggZ9E6xBzUL_text","default":"<p>These aren't marketing statistics manufactured by an advertising agency. These are outcomes tracked by pharmacists across Italy who recommend this product to their patients and follow up on results.</p>"}],
